Simply the BEST Action-Adventure ever made!

This game improves all the good things of the first Chapter, and corrects all the bad things about Castlevania Lords of Shadow. The Metacritic medium rank, 5,8/10, is simply ridiculous; I think that it deserves a full 10/10.

The good:
- awesome graphics, much better then in Castlevania 1 and with fluider animations;
- excellent gameplay (and, this time, with a mobile camera);
- the BEST Boss battles ever made;
- wonderful environments, a bit less various then in Castlevania 1 but even more beautiful;
- you start as a villain, and finish recovering your humanity.

The bad: there isn't anything wrong about this game.

In conclusion, for me this game is far better then the first chapter and I can't really understand the reason why videogame critics have judged it so badly.
